# Firebase Configuration
# Get these values from your Firebase project settings

NEXT_PUBLIC_FIREBASE_API_KEY=your_firebase_api_key_here
NEXT_PUBLIC_FIREBASE_AUTH_DOMAIN=your_project_id.firebaseapp.com
NEXT_PUBLIC_FIREBASE_PROJECT_ID=your_project_id_here
NEXT_PUBLIC_FIREBASE_STORAGE_BUCKET=your_project_id.appspot.com
NEXT_PUBLIC_FIREBASE_MESSAGING_SENDER_ID=your_messaging_sender_id_here
NEXT_PUBLIC_FIREBASE_APP_ID=your_firebase_app_id_here

# Instructions:
# 1. Go to https://console.firebase.google.com/
# 2. Create a new project or select an existing one
# 3. Go to Project Settings > General tab
# 4. Scroll down to "Your apps" section
# 5. Click "Web app" and register your app
# 6. Copy the config values and replace the placeholders above
# 7. Save this file as .env.local in your project root
#
# Enable Authentication:
# 1. In Firebase Console, go to Authentication > Sign-in method
# 2. Enable Google as a sign-in provider
# 3. Add your domain (localhost:3000 for development) to authorized domains
#
# Enable Firestore:
# 1. In Firebase Console, go to Firestore Database
# 2. Click "Create database"
# 3. Choose your security rules (start in test mode for development)